No, yes, but הלכה, halacha if it actually walked, אינה צריכה בדיקה.

1209
00:56:37,580 --> 00:56:41,260
eina tzricha bedika. That's the best. Then not only do you not

1210
00:56:41,260 --> 00:56:42,790
have to wait 24 hours and it doesn't have ריסוק איברים, risuk

1211
00:56:42,790 --> 00:56:45,720
evarim you don't have to worry and do any internal check. So

1212
00:56:45,880 --> 00:56:49,740
one stage: if you didn't wait, no internal check will help. If

1213
00:56:49,740 --> 00:56:51,440
you did wait or it stood up, it gets out of the

1214
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:54,980
ריסוק איברים problem, but an internal check is still needed. And if

1215
00:56:54,980 --> 00:56:58,160
it walked, you don't even need an internal check. רב חייא בר

1216
00:56:58,200 --> 00:56:59,125
אשי אמר: Rav Chiya bar Ashi amar: אחזו ואחזו צריכה בדיקה. achazu

1217
00:56:59,125 --> 00:57:02,660
ve'achazu tzricha bedika. He said even walking needs an internal check. We

1218
00:57:02,660 --> 00:57:04,031
don't rule that way. אמר רב ירמיה בר אבא אמר רב: Amar

1219
00:57:04,031 --> 00:57:06,920
Rav Yirmeya bar Abba amar Rav: פשטה ידה לעמוד, pashta yada l'amod,

1220
00:57:07,060 --> 00:57:09,560
and maybe you don't even need it to stand up. Maybe if

1221
00:57:09,560 --> 00:57:12,500
it just stretches out its arm and shows that it's trying to

1222
00:57:12,500 --> 00:57:14,520
stand up, אף על פי שלא עמדה, af al pi shelo amda,

1223
00:57:14,600 --> 00:57:16,320
that would be even if it didn't stand, that would be good

1224
00:57:16,320 --> 00:57:19,680
enough. עקרה רגלה להלך, akra ragla l'halech, if it moved its leg

1225
00:57:19,680 --> 00:57:21,900
to walk, אף על פי שלא הלכה, af al pi shelo halcha,

1226
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:24,793
even without walking, so even that suffices. ורב חסדא אמר: V'Rav Chisda

1227
00:57:24,793 --> 00:57:25,300
amar: ניערה

1228
00:57:26,340 --> 00:57:27,732
לעמוד, niera l'amod, אף על פי שלא עמדה. af al pi shelo

1229
00:57:27,732 --> 00:57:29,900
amda. Even if it didn't stick out its leg, even if it

1230
00:57:29,900 --> 00:57:32,860
only started moving its body to show it was trying to stand,

1231
00:57:32,960 --> 00:57:35,660
that counts as standing. Now there's a whole question about this next

1232
00:57:35,660 --> 00:57:38,440
line. This is probably a later גאוני Geonic gloss, but we'll read

1233
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:42,200
it: והלכתא, vehilchasa, the הלכה is, היכא דנפלה מן הגג בלא ידעה,

1234
00:57:40,200 --> 00:57:43,340
heicha d'nafla min hagag bidlo yada, if it fell off the roof

1235
00:57:43,340 --> 00:57:46,960
without knowing, meaning it didn't jump or and it fell off presumably

1236
00:57:46,960 --> 00:57:51,040
back-first also, ועמדה ולא הלכה, ve'amda v'lo halcha, so if it stood

1237
00:57:51,040 --> 00:57:54,580
without walking, צריכה בדיקה, tzricha bedika, it needs checking, ואינה צריכה מעת

1238
00:57:54,580 --> 00:57:56,380
לעת, v'eina tzricha me'eis le'eis, not 24 hours, ואם הלכה אפילו בדיקה

1239
00:57:56,380 --> 00:57:58,100
נמי לא צריכה, v'im halcha afilu bedika nami lo tzricha, if it

1240
00:57:58,100 --> 00:58:00,200
walked, you don't need to check, so we do rule that with

1241
00:58:00,200 --> 00:58:02,660
walking you don't need to check. But we also rule that it

1242
00:58:02,660 --> 00:58:06,500
needs to really stand or really walk. Just attempting to stand, attempting

1243
00:58:06,500 --> 00:58:10,760
to walk is not sufficient. Okay, I guess we will have to

1244
00:58:10,760 --> 00:58:12,540
end here. We'll have to make it up later.
